    "# Learning Uncertainty Sets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 83,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cvxpy as cp\n",
    "import scipy as sc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import numpy.random as npr\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "from sklearn import datasets\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import lro\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    \"text.usetex\":True,\n",
    "    \n",
    "    \"font.size\":18,\n",
    "    \"font.family\": \"serif\"\n",
    "})\n",
    "colors = [\"tab:blue\", \"tab:green\", \"tab:orange\", \n",
    "          \"blue\", \"tab:purple\", \"tab:brown\", \"tab:pink\", \"tab:grey\", \"tab:olive\"]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 84,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def pareto_frontier(Xs, Ys, maxX = False, maxY = False):\n",
    "# Sort the list in either ascending or descending order of X\n",
    "    Xs = np.array(Xs)\n",
    "    Ys = np.array(Ys)\n",
    "    myList = sorted([[Xs[i], Ys[i]] for i in range(len(Xs))], reverse=maxX)\n",
    "# Start the Pareto frontier with the first value in the sorted list\n",
    "    p_front = [myList[0]]    \n",
    "# Loop through the sorted list\n",
    "    for pair in myList[1:]:\n",
    "        if maxY: \n",
    "            if pair[1] >= p_front[-1][1]: # Look for higher values of Y…\n",
    "                p_front.append(pair) # … and add them to the Pareto frontier\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            if pair[1] <= p_front[-1][1]: # Look for lower values of Y…\n",
    "                p_front.append(pair) # … and add them to the Pareto frontier\n",
    "# Turn resulting pairs back into a list of Xs and Ys\n",
    "    p_frontX = [pair[0] for pair in p_front]\n",
    "    p_frontY = [pair[1] for pair in p_front]\n",
    "    return p_frontX, p_frontY"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Formulating the uncertainty set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We now formulate the uncertainty set slightly differently, where data and a loss function is passed as parameters instead of the uncertainty set parameters. The parameters for the uncertainty set, $A$ and $b$, will now be trained through differentiable optimization. \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Ellipsoidal uncertainty: $\\{u \\mid \\| Au + b \\|_p \\leq 1 \\}$ \n",
    "\n",
    "- $p$ : integer, optional  \n",
    "  * Order of the norm. Default 2.\n",
    "- data : np.array  \n",
    "  * An array of uncertainty realizations, where each row is one realization.\n",
    "- loss : function\n",
    "  * The loss function used to train the uncertainty set. \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Mean Robust uncertainty: $\\{ u = (v_1,\\dots,v_K)  \\mid  \\sum_{k=1} ^K w_k \\| A_k(v_k - \\bar{d}_k) \\|_p^{\\text{power}} \\le \\rho \\}$ \n",
    "\n",
    "- $K$: int\n",
    "  * Number of clusters. Default 1.\n",
    "- $p$ : integer, optional  \n",
    "  * Order of the norm. Default 2.\n",
    "- power: integer, optional\n",
    "  * Power of the norm. Default 1. \n",
    "- data : np.array  \n",
    "  * An array of uncertainty realizations, where each row is one realization.\n",
    "- loss : function\n",
    "  * The loss function used to train the uncertainty set. \n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "### Box uncertainty: $\\{ u \\mid\\| Au + b \\|_\\infty \\leq 1 \\}$ \n",
    "\n",
    "- data : np.array  \n",
    "  * An array of uncertainty realizations, where each row is one realization.\n",
    "- loss : function\n",
    "  * The loss function used to train the uncertainty set. \n",
    "\n",
    "### Budget uncertainty: \n",
    "\n",
    "1. train the box portion only: $\\{u \\mid \\| Au + b \\|_\\infty \\leq 1, \\| u \\|_1 \\leq \\rho_2\\}$ \n",
    "2. train the 1-norm portion only: $\\{u \\mid \\| u \\|_\\infty \\leq \\rho_1, \\| Au + b \\|_1 \\leq 1\\}$ \n",
    "- train_box: boolean, optional\n",
    "  * If True, train the box portion only. Default True. \n",
    "- $\\rho_1$ : float, optional\n",
    "  * Box scaling. Default 1.0.\n",
    "- $\\rho_2$ : float, optional\n",
    "  * 1-norm scaling. Default 1.0.\n",
    "- data : np.array  \n",
    "  * An array of uncertainty realizations, where each row is one realization.\n",
    "- loss : function\n",
    "  * The loss function used to train the uncertainty set.\n",
    "  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Formulating the loss function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The loss function passed into the uncertainty set must be a function that returns torch tensors with gradient information. The function must take in as inputs all the variables defined in the Robust Problem, as well as the data used to evaluate the loss. There may also be other inputs to the function, depending on the type of loss.  \n",
    "An example of a violation loss is \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\mathcal{L}(\\mathcal{D}, x) = f(x)  + \\frac{\\lambda }{N}\\sum_{i=1}^{N} g(d_i,x)_+,\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $\\mathcal{D}$ is the dataset, $\\lambda$ is the weight on the violation loss, $N$ is the total number of datapoints in the dataset, and $d_i$ is sample $i$ of the dataset. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Training the uncertainty set\n",
    "\n",
    "To train the uncertainty set, after setting up the robust problem, call `problem.train()`, with optional parameters to control whether to train only $\\epsilon$ or both $A$ and $b$, the total number of iterations, the learning rate of the problem, the optimizer to use, and initial values for $A$ and $b$. \n",
    "\n",
    "The function will return a pandas DataFrame with information on the iterates, as well as the reformulated problem.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 1: Linear Portfolio\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Consider the simple portfolio problem where we want to select a portfolio of stocks that maximizes returns. The Robust Problem is formulated as\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{array}{ll}\n",
    "\\text{minimize} & \\tau\\\\\n",
    "\\text{subject to}  & -u^Tx \\leq  \\tau\\\\\n",
    "&\\mathbf{1}^Tx = 1, x \\geq 0,\n",
    "\\end{array}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $u$ is the uncertain parameter. \n",
    "\n",
    "We train an ellipsoidal uncertainty set with $p = 2$, and consider the violation loss $\\tau + \\lambda(-u^Tx - \\tau)_+$, where $\\lambda = 1$ is the scaling for the sum of violations. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 85,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# The violation loss function, in torch tensors\n",
    "def violation_loss(t_soln, x_soln, data, lmbda=1):\n",
    "    return t_soln + lmbda * torch.mean(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(-data @ x_soln - t_soln, torch.tensor(0., requires_grad=True))), t_soln,  torch.mean(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(-data @ x_soln - t_soln, torch.tensor(0., requires_grad=True)))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Functions to generate data\n",
    "def normal_returns_scaled(N, m, scale):\n",
    "    R = np.vstack([np.random.normal(\n",
    "        i*0.03*scale, np.sqrt((0.02**2+(i*0.025)**2)), N) for i in range(1, m+1)])\n",
    "    return (R.transpose())\n",
    "\n",
    "def data_modes(N, m, scales):\n",
    "    modes = len(scales)\n",
    "    d = np.zeros((N+100, m))\n",
    "    weights = int(np.ceil(N/modes))\n",
    "    for i in range(modes):\n",
    "        d[i*weights:(i+1)*weights,\n",
    "          :] = normal_returns_scaled(weights, m, scales[i])\n",
    "    return d[0:N, :]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data\n",
    "num_stocks = 2\n",
    "N = 100\n",
    "data = data_modes(N,num_stocks,[1,2,3])"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Formulate the uncertainty set and uncertain parameter\n",
    "unc_set = lro.Ellipsoidal(data=data, loss=violation_loss)\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(num_stocks, uncertainty_set=unc_set)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x = cp.Variable(num_stocks)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t)\n",
    "cons = [-u @ x <= t]\n",
    "cons += [cp.sum(x) == 1, x >= 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob_robust = lro.RobustProblem(objective, cons)\n",
    "s = 20\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train only epsilon\n",
    "result = prob_robust.train(eps=True, lr=0.1, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", init_eps = 1, seed = s)\n",
    "df = result.df\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob_robust.train(lr=0.1, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result2 = prob_robust.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.3, 5, 50), seed = s)\n",
    "dfgrid = result2.df\n",
    "# Plot results\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 4.5))\n",
    "ax1.plot(df['step'], df['Loss_val'], color=\"tab:blue\", label=r\"$\\epsilon$ training\")\n",
    "ax1.plot(df['step'], df['Eval_val'], linestyle='--', color=\"tab:blue\", label=r\"$\\epsilon$ testing\")\n",
    "ax1.plot(df1['step'], df1['Loss_val'], color=\"tab:orange\", label=\"Reshape training\")\n",
    "ax1.plot(df1['step'], df1['Eval_val'], linestyle='--', color=\"tab:orange\", label=\"Reshape testing\")\n",
    "ax1.legend()\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel(\"Iterations\")\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 2: Quadratic uncertainty\n",
    "We consider a problem with quadratic uncertainty, \n",
    "\n",
    "$$g(u,x) = \\sum_{i=1}^n g_i(u,x), \\quad \\text{where } \\quad g_i(u,x) = -(1/2)u^T(P_ix_i)u.$$ \n",
    "We have each $P_i\\in \\mathbf{R}^{n\\times n}$ a symmetric positive definite matrix, $u \\in \\mathbf{R}^n$ from an ellipsoidal set, and $x \\in \\mathbf{R}^{n}_{+}$. \n",
    "The robust formulation is \n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{array}{ll}\n",
    "\\text{minimize} & \\tau\\\\\n",
    "\\text{subject to}  & -(1/2)\\sum_{i=1}^n (u^TP_iu)x_i  \\leq  \\tau \\quad \\forall u \\in \\mathcal{U}(\\theta)\\\\\n",
    "& \\mathbf{1}^Tx = 1\\\\\n",
    "& x \\geq 0, \\quad x \\leq 1,\n",
    "\\end{array}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\theta$ encodes the training parameters $(A,b)$. We again consider the violation loss."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define the loss function\n",
    "def loss(t,x,data,l = 2): \n",
    "    cur_sum = 0\n",
    "    for i in range(data.shape[0]):\n",
    "        cur_sum = cur_sum + torch.maximum(torch.sum(torch.tensor([-0.5*data[i]@torch.tensor(P[ind],requires_grad = True)\n",
    "                                                                  *x[ind]@data[i] for ind in range(n)], requires_grad = True)) - t, \n",
    "                                          torch.tensor(0., requires_grad=True))\n",
    "    return t + l*cur_sum/data.shape[0], t, cur_sum/data.shape[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "#Generate data\n",
    "P = {}\n",
    "P_inv = {}\n",
    "n = 2\n",
    "N = 50\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    P[i] = datasets.make_spd_matrix(n, random_state=i)\n",
    "    P_inv[i] = sc.linalg.sqrtm(np.linalg.inv(P[i]))\n",
    "data = data_modes(N,n,[1,2,3])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate the uncertainty set and uncertain parameter\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                        uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "                                                    data = data, \n",
    "                                                    loss = loss))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t)\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints = [cp.sum([-0.5*lro.uncertain_atoms.quad_form.quad_form(u, P[i]*x[i]) for i in range(n)]) <= t]\n",
    "constraints += [cp.sum(x)==1]\n",
    "constraints += [x >= 0, x <= 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "\n",
    "s = 135\n",
    "# Train only epsilon\n",
    "result = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.1, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", init_eps = 0.4, seed = s)\n",
    "df_eps = result.df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.1, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "result2 = prob.train(lr = 0.1, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s)\n",
    "df2 = result2.df\n",
    "A_fin = result2.A\n",
    "b_fin = result2.b\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result3 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.3, 2, 40), seed = s)\n",
    "dfgrid = result3.df"
   ]
  },

    "ax2.plot(dfgrid[\"Eps\"], dfgrid[\"Eval_val\"], color = colors[j], linestyle='--',label=\"$\\epsilon$ grid\")\n",
    "ax2.plot(df_eps[\"A_norm\"],df_eps[\"Eval_val\"], linestyle='-', marker=styles[j], color = \"blue\", label=\"$\\epsilon$ SGD\",alpha = 0.7)\n",
    "ax2.hlines( xmin = np.min(dfgrid[\"Eps\"]), xmax = np.max(dfgrid[\"Eps\"]), y = np.min(df1[\"Eval_val\"]), label = \"$R$ best\", color= \"red\")   \n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel(\"$\\epsilon$\")\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Testing loss\")\n",
    "ax2.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 3: Max of affine uncertainty\n",
    "We consider a problem with max of affine uncertainty, \n",
    "\n",
    "$$g(u,x) = \\max_{l=1,\\dots,L} (P_lu + a_l)^Tx,$$\n",
    "where $P_l$ and $a_l$ are constants for all $l = 1, \\dots, L$. The robust formulation is \n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\begin{array}{ll}\n",
    "\\text{minimize} & \\tau\\\\\n",
    "\\text{subject to}  & \\max_{l=1,\\dots,L} (P_lu + a_l)^Tx  \\leq  \\tau \\quad \\forall u \\in \\mathcal{U}(\\theta)\\\\\n",
    "& x \\geq 0,\n",
    "\\end{array}\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "where $\\theta$ encodes the training parameters $(A,b)$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate constants\n",
    "n = 2\n",
    "N = 50\n",
    "# k = npr.uniform(1,4,n)\n",
    "# p = k + npr.uniform(2,5,n)\n",
    "k = np.array([4.,5.])\n",
    "p = np.array([5,6.5])\n",
    "k_tch = torch.tensor(k, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p_tch = torch.tensor(p, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "k1 = np.array([0.5,1.])\n",
    "p1 = np.array([3.,1.5])\n",
    "k1_tch = torch.tensor(k1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p1_tch = torch.tensor(p1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "b = npr.uniform(1,3,2)\n",
    "b_tch = torch.tensor(b, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "# Formulate loss function\n",
    "def loss(t,y,x, x1, data,l = 5): \n",
    "    return t +y + l*torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))+ l*torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x) - y, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))), t+y, torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))+ torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x) - y, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))\n",
    "#+ torch.maximum(k_tch@(x - b_tch),torch.tensor(0.))\n",
    "def gen_demand(n, N):\n",
    "    F = np.random.normal(size = (n,2))\n",
    "    sig = 0.1*F@(F.T)\n",
    "    mu = np.random.uniform(-0.2,3,n)\n",
    "    norms = np.random.multivariate_normal(mu,sig, N)\n",
    "    d_train = np.exp(norms)\n",
    "    return d_train\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data\n",
    "data = gen_demand(n,N)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate uncertainty set\n",
    "# u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "#                         uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "#                                                     data=data, loss = loss))\n",
    "K = 5\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                        uncertainty_set=lro.MRO(K = K, p=2,\n",
    "                                                    data=data, loss = loss, uniqueA = True))\n",
    "Astart = u.uncertainty_set._init_A\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "\n",
    "s = 13\n",
    "# # Train only epsilon\n",
    "# result = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", init_eps = 1, seed = s)\n",
    "# df_eps = result.df\n",
    "# # Train A and b\n",
    "# df1, newprob, A_fin, b_fin = prob.train(lr = 0.01, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_eps=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Grid search epsilon\n",
    "# dfgrid, newprob = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.8, 2, 40), seed = s)\n",
    "init = sc.linalg.sqrtm(sc.linalg.inv(np.cov(data.T)))\n",
    "init_bval = -init@np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.001, step=200, momentum = 0.8, scheduler = True, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = init, init_b = init_bval, fixb = False)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "result2 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, scheduler = True, step= 200, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin)\n",
    "df_r1 = result2.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result3 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, scheduler = True, step=200, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = init, init_b = init_bval)\n",
    "df_r2 = result3.df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result4 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.001, 2, 40), init_A = init, init_b = init_bval, seed = s)\n",
    "dfgrid = result4.df"
   ]
  },

    "def fmt(x):\n",
    "    s = f\"{x:.1f}\"\n",
    "    if s.endswith(\"0\"):\n",
    "        s = f\"{x:.0f}\"\n",
    "    return rf\"{s}\" if plt.rcParams[\"text.usetex\"] else f\"{s}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",
    "num_p = 50\n",
    "offset = 2\n",
    "x_min, x_max = np.min(data[:,0]) - offset, np.max(data[:,0]) + offset\n",
    "y_min, y_max = np.min(data[:,1]) - offset, np.max(data[:,1]) + offset\n",
    "X = np.linspace(x_min,x_max,num_p)\n",
    "Y = np.linspace(y_min,y_max,num_p)\n",
    "x,y = np.meshgrid(X,Y)\n",
    "# Z values as a matrix\n",
    "fin_set = {}\n",
    "init_set = {}\n",
    "for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "    fin_set[k_ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "    init_set[k_ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "      \n",

    "g_level_learned1 = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",

    "\n",

    "#     for j in range(num_p):\n",
    "#         u_vec = [x[i,j], y[i,j]]\n",

    "\n",
    "# Populate Z Values (a 7x7 matrix) - For a circle x^2+y^2=z\n",
    "for i in range(num_p):\n",
    "    for j in range(num_p):\n",
    "        u_vec = [x[i,j], y[i,j]]\n",
    "        for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "            fin_set[k_ind][i,j] = np.linalg.norm(A_fin[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@ u_vec  - A_fin[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@u.uncertainty_set.Dbar[k_ind])\n",
    "\n",
    "        for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "            init_set[k_ind][i,j] = np.linalg.norm(result3.A[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@ u_vec  - result3.A[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@u.uncertainty_set.Dbar[k_ind])\n",

    "# Formulate uncertainty set\n",
    "# u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "#                         uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "#                                                     data=data, loss = loss))\n",
    "K = 5\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                        uncertainty_set=lro.MRO(K = K, p=2,\n",
    "                                                    data=data, loss = loss, uniqueA = True))\n",
    "Astart = u.uncertainty_set._init_A\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "\n",
    "s = 13\n",
    "# # Train only epsilon\n",
    "# result = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", init_eps = 1, seed = s)\n",
    "# df_eps = result.df\n",
    "# # Train A and b\n",
    "# df1, newprob, A_fin, b_fin = prob.train(lr = 0.01, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_eps=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Grid search epsilon\n",
    "# dfgrid, newprob = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.8, 2, 40), seed = s)\n",
    "init = sc.linalg.sqrtm(sc.linalg.inv(np.cov(data.T)))\n",
    "init_bval = -init@np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.001, step=200, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = None, init_b = init_bval, fixb = False)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "result2 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step= 200, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin)\n",
    "df_r1 = result2.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result3 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=200, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = None, init_b = init_bval )\n",

    "    s = f\"{x:.1f}\"\n",
    "    if s.endswith(\"0\"):\n",

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate constants\n",
    "n = 2\n",
    "N = 50\n",
    "# k = npr.uniform(1,4,n)\n",
    "# p = k + npr.uniform(2,5,n)\n",
    "k = np.array([4.,5.])\n",
    "p = np.array([5,6.5])\n",
    "k_tch = torch.tensor(k, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p_tch = torch.tensor(p, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "k1 = np.array([1.,1.])\n",
    "p1 = np.array([4.,1.5])\n",
    "k1_tch = torch.tensor(k1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p1_tch = torch.tensor(p1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "b = npr.uniform(1,3,2)\n",
    "b_tch = torch.tensor(b, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "# Formulate loss function\n",
    "def loss(t,y,x, x1, data,l = 5): \n",
    "    return t +y + l*torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))+ l*torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x1) - y, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))), t+y, torch.mean((((torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001).float()+ (torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x1) - y, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001).float())>=1).float())\n",
    "#+ torch.maximum(k_tch@(x - b_tch),torch.tensor(0.))\n",
    "\n",
    "def gen_demand(n, N):\n",
    "    F = np.random.normal(size = (n,2))\n",
    "    sig = 0.1*F@(F.T)\n",
    "    mu = np.random.uniform(-0.2,3,n)\n",
    "    norms = np.random.multivariate_normal(mu,sig, N)\n",
    "    d_train = np.exp(norms)\n",
    "    return d_train\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data\n",
    "data = gen_demand(n,N)\n",
    "data = np.load(\"data.npy\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate uncertainty set\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                        uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "                                                    data=data, loss = loss))\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1, x_1 >= 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "\n",
    "s = 13\n",
    "# # Train only epsilon\n",
    "# result = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", init_eps = 1, seed = s)\n",
    "# df_eps = result.df\n",
    "# # Train A and b\n",
    "# df1, newprob, A_fin, b_fin = prob.train(lr = 0.01, step=50, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_eps=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Grid search epsilon\n",
    "# dfgrid, newprob = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.8, 2, 40), seed = s)\n",
    "init = sc.linalg.sqrtm(sc.linalg.inv(np.cov(data.T)))\n",
    "init_bval = -init@np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.001, step=100, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = init, init_b = init_bval, fixb = False)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "result2 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step= 100, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin)\n",
    "df_r1 = result2.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result3 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=100, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = init, init_b = init_bval )\n",
    "df_r2 = result3.df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result4 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.01, 3, 40), init_A = result3.A, init_b = result3.b, seed = s)\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_opt_base = {}\n",
    "x_opt_base1 = {}\n",
    "x_opt_learned = {}\n",
    "x_opt_learned1 = {}\n",
    "t_learned = {}\n",
    "t_base = {}\n",
    "for ind in range(4):\n",
    "    n = 2\n",
    "    u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                            uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "                                                        A = (1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*result3.A, b = result3.b))\n",
    "    # Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "    x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "    x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "    t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "    y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "    objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "    constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "    constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1, x_1 >= 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "    prob.solve()\n",
    "    # result3.reform_problem.solve()\n",
    "    x_opt_base[ind] = x_r.value\n",
    "    x_opt_base1[ind] = x_1.value\n",
    "\n",
    "    t_base[ind] = t.value + y.value\n",
    "\n",
    "    n = 2\n",
    "    u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                            uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "                                                        A = (1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*A_fin, b = b_fin))\n",
    "    # Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "    x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "    x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "    t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "    y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "    objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "    constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "    constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "    constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1, x_1 >= 0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "    prob.solve()\n",
    "    # result3.reform_problem.solve()\n",
    "    x_opt_learned[ind] = x_r.value\n",
    "    x_opt_learned1[ind] = x_1.value\n",
    "\n",
    "    t_learned[ind] = t.value + y.value\n",
    "    x_opt_learned,x_opt_base,x_opt_learned1,x_opt_base1,t_learned, t_base\n",
    "    # A_fin, init, b_fin, init_bval"
   ]

    "def fmt(x):\n",
    "    s = f\"{x:.1f}\"\n",
    "    if s.endswith(\"0\"):\n",
    "        s = f\"{x:.0f}\"\n",
    "    return rf\"{s}\" if plt.rcParams[\"text.usetex\"] else f\"{s}\"\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",
    "num_p = 50\n",
    "offset = 2\n",
    "x_min, x_max = np.min(data[:,0]) - offset, np.max(data[:,0]) + offset\n",
    "y_min, y_max = np.min(data[:,1]) - offset, np.max(data[:,1]) + offset\n",
    "X = np.linspace(x_min,x_max,num_p)\n",
    "Y = np.linspace(y_min,y_max,num_p)\n",
    "x,y = np.meshgrid(X,Y)\n",
    "# Z values as a matrix\n",
    "fin_set = {}\n",
    "init_set = {}\n",
    "for ind in range(4):\n",
    "    fin_set[ind] = {}\n",
    "    init_set[ind] = {}\n",
    "    for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "        fin_set[ind][k_ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "        init_set[ind][k_ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "      \n",
    "\n",
    "g_level_learned = {}\n",
    "g_level_base = {}\n",
    "g_level_learned1 = {}\n",
    "g_level_base1 = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for ind in range(4):\n",
    "# init_set = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "    g_level_learned[ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "    g_level_base[ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "    g_level_learned1[ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "    g_level_base1[ind] = np.zeros((num_p,num_p))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # # Populate Z Values (a 7x7 matrix) - For a circle x^2+y^2=z\n",
    "    # for i in range(num_p):\n",
    "    #     for j in range(num_p):\n",
    "    #         u_vec = [x[i,j], y[i,j]]\n",
    "    #         fin_set[i,j] = np.linalg.norm(A_fin@ u_vec  + b_fin)\n",
    "    #         init_set[i,j] = np.linalg.norm(init@ u_vec + init_bval)\n",
    "    #         g_level_learned[i,j] = np.maximum(k @ x_opt_learned - p @ x_opt_learned, k @ x_opt_learned - p @ u_vec)\n",
    "    #         g_level_base[i,j] = np.maximum(k @ x_opt_base - p @ x_opt_base, k @ x_opt_base - p @ u_vec)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Populate Z Values (a 7x7 matrix) - For a circle x^2+y^2=z\n",
    "    for i in range(num_p):\n",
    "        for j in range(num_p):\n",
    "            u_vec = [x[i,j], y[i,j]]\n",
    "            for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "                fin_set[ind][k_ind][i,j] = np.linalg.norm((1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*A_fin[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@ u_vec  - (1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*A_fin[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@np.mean(data, axis = 0))\n",
    "\n",
    "            for k_ind in range(K):\n",
    "                init_set[ind][k_ind][i,j] = np.linalg.norm((1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*result3.A[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@ u_vec  - (1/eps_list[inds[ind]])*result3.A[k_ind*n:(k_ind+1)*n, 0:n]@np.mean(data, axis = 0))\n",
    "            # init_set[i,j] = np.linalg.norm(init@ u_vec - init@np.mean(data, axis = 0))\n",
    "            g_level_learned[ind][i,j] = np.maximum(k @ x_opt_learned[ind] - p @ x_opt_learned[ind], k @ x_opt_learned[ind] - p @ u_vec) + np.maximum(k1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind] - p1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind], k1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind] - p1 @ u_vec)\n",
    "            g_level_base[ind][i,j] = np.maximum(k @ x_opt_base[ind] - p @ x_opt_base[ind], k @ x_opt_base[ind] - p @ u_vec) + np.maximum(k1 @ x_opt_base1[ind] - p1 @ x_opt_base1[ind], k1 @ x_opt_base1[ind] - p1 @ u_vec)\n",
    "            g_level_learned1[ind][i,j] = np.maximum(k1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind] - p1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind], k1 @ x_opt_learned1[ind] - p1 @ u_vec)\n",
    "            g_level_base1[ind][i,j] = np.maximum(k1 @ x_opt_base1[ind] - p1 @ x_opt_base1[ind], k1 @ x_opt_base1[ind] - p1 @ u_vec)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3, ax4) = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(16, 3))\n",

    "### Larger Newsvendor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Formulate constants\n",
    "n = 15\n",
    "N = 300\n",
    "k = npr.uniform(2,5,n)\n",
    "p = k + npr.uniform(1,3,n)\n",
    "k1 = npr.uniform(1,3,n)\n",
    "p1 = k1 + npr.uniform(0,2,n)\n",
    "# k = np.array([4.,5.])\n",
    "# p = np.array([5,6.5])\n",
    "k_tch = torch.tensor(k, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p_tch = torch.tensor(p, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "k1_tch = torch.tensor(k1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "p1_tch = torch.tensor(p1, requires_grad = True)\n",
    "\n",
    "def loss(t,x,alpha,data, mu = 1, l = 5, quantile = 0.95,target = 0.): \n",
    "    sums = torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum( k_tch@x -data@(p_tch), k_tch@x - x@(p_tch)) - t - alpha, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))\n",
    "    sums = sums/(1-quantile) + alpha\n",
    "    return t + l*(sums - target) + (mu/2)*(sums - target)**2, t, torch.mean((torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@(p_tch), k_tch@x - x@(p_tch)) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001).float()), sums.detach().numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "def loss(t,y,x, x1, alpha, data, mu = 5, l=10, quantile = 0.95, target = 0.):\n",
    "    sums =  torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t-alpha, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))+ torch.mean(torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x) - y-alpha, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))\n",
    "    sums = sums/(2*(1-quantile)) + alpha\n",
    "    return t +y + l*(sums - target) + (mu/2)*(sums - target)**2, t+y, 0.5*torch.mean((torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k_tch@x -data@p_tch, k_tch@x - p_tch@x) - t, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001).float()) + 0.5*torch.mean((torch.maximum(\n",
    "        torch.maximum(k1_tch@x1 -data@p1_tch, k1_tch@x1 - p1_tch@x) - y, \n",
    "        torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001).float()), sums.detach().numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "def gen_demand(n, N):\n",
    "    F = np.random.normal(size = (n,2))\n",
    "    sig = 0.1*F@(F.T)\n",
    "    mu = np.random.uniform(-0.2,2,n)\n",
    "    norms = np.random.multivariate_normal(mu,sig, N)\n",
    "    d_train = np.exp(norms)\n",
    "    return d_train\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate data\n",
    "data = gen_demand(n,N)\n",
    "# data = np.load(\"data4.npy\")\n",
    "# np.save(\"data4.npy\", data)"
   ]

    "# data = gen_demand(n,N)\n",
    "# Formulate uncertainty set\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(n,\n",
    "                        uncertainty_set=lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2,\n",
    "                                                    data=data, loss = loss))\n",
    "# Formulate the Robust Problem\n",
    "x_r = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "x_1 = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "t = cp.Variable()\n",
    "y = cp.Variable()\n",
    "\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(t+y)\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints = [cp.maximum(k@x_r - p@x_r, k@x_r - p@u) <= t]\n",
    "constraints += [cp.maximum(k1@x_1 - p1@x_1, k1@x_1 - p1@u) <= y]\n",
    "\n",
    "constraints += [x_r >= 0, x_r >= x_1]\n",
    "\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "target = 0.\n",
    "s = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Grid search epsilon\n",
    "# dfgrid, newprob = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.8, 2, 40), seed = s)\n",
    "init = sc.linalg.sqrtm(sc.linalg.inv(np.cov(data.T)))\n",
    "init_bval = -init@np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "# Train A and b\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.00001, step=500, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = 0.2*init, init_b = 0.2*init_bval, fixb = False, init_mu = 5, init_lam = 10, target_cvar = target, init_alpha = 0., mu_multiplier = 1.01)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "# result2 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.001, step=500, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin, init_mu = 1, init_lam = 5, target_cvar = target, init_alpha = 0.)\n",
    "# df_r1 = result2.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result3 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.00001, step=500, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = 0.2*init, init_b = 0.2*init_bval, init_mu = 5, init_lam = 10,  target_cvar = target, init_alpha =0.,mu_multiplier = 1.01)\n",
    "df_r2 = result3.df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result4 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.01, 3, 40), init_A = result3.A, init_b = result3.b, seed = s, init_alpha = 0.)\n",
    "dfgrid = result4.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result5 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.01, 3, 40), init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin, seed = s, init_alpha = 0.)\n",
    "dfgrid2 = result5.df"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Example 4: Affine Adjustable Robust Optimization: Inventory management\n",
    "\n",
    "We solve the robust optimization problem given as \n",
    "\\begin{equation*}\n",
    "\t\\begin{array}{ll}\n",
    "\t\t\\text{minimize} & L\\\\\n",
    "\t\t\\text{subject to} & -r^Ty^0 - r^TYu + (t+h)^Ts \\le L, \\quad \\forall u\\in \\mathcal{U}(\\mathcal{D}_N,\\theta)\\\\\n",
    "\t\t& y^0_i + y_i^Tu\\leq s_i, \\quad i = 1, \\dots, N, \\quad \\forall u\\in \\mathcal{U}(\\mathcal{D}_N,\\theta)\\\\\n",
    "\t\t& y^0_i + y_i^Tu \\leq d_i^0 + q_i^Tu, \\quad i = 1, \\dots, N, \\quad \\forall u\\in \\mathcal{U}(\\mathcal{D}_N,\\theta)\\\\\n",
    "\t\t\t& \\mathbf{1}^Ts = C\\\\\n",
    "\t\t\t& s \\leq c\\\\\n",
    "\t\t\t& s \\geq 0.\n",
    "\t\\end{array}\n",
    "\\end{equation*}\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 92,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def loss(L,y,Y,s,alpha, data,mu=100,l=1000,quantile = 0.95, target = -0.1):\n",
    "    sums = 0\n",
    "    totsum = 0\n",
    "    Nsample = data.shape[0]\n",
    "    for i in range(Nsample):\n",
    "        sums += torch.sum(torch.maximum(y + Y@data[i] - s-alpha, torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))\n",
    "        sums += torch.sum(torch.maximum(y + Y@data[i] - torch.tensor(d) - torch.tensor(Q)@data[i] - alpha, torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True)))\n",
    "        sums += torch.maximum(-torch.tensor(r)@y - torch.tensor(r)@Y@data[i] + torch.tensor(t+ h)@s - L - alpha, torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))\n",
    "\n",
    "        newsums = torch.sum(torch.where(torch.maximum(y + Y@data[i] - s, torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001,torch.tensor(1.), torch.tensor(0.)))\n",
    "        newsums += torch.sum(torch.where(torch.maximum(y + Y@data[i] - torch.tensor(d) - torch.tensor(Q)@data[i], torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.001,torch.tensor(1.), torch.tensor(0.)))\n",
    "        newsums += torch.where(torch.maximum(-torch.tensor(r)@y - torch.tensor(r)@Y@data[i] + torch.tensor(t+ h)@s - L, torch.tensor(0.,requires_grad = True))>=0.01, torch.tensor(1.), torch.tensor(0.))\n",
    "        totsum += newsums/(2*10+1)\n",
    "    sums = (sums/((1-quantile)*(2*10+1)*Nsample)) + alpha\n",
    "    return L + torch.tensor(l)*(sums - torch.tensor(target)) + torch.tensor(mu/2)*(sums - torch.tensor(target))**2, L, totsum/Nsample, sums.detach().numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "#torch.tensor(totsum/Nsample)\n",
    "n = 10\n",
    "m = 4\n",
    "# data = np.random.normal(0,3,(400,m))\n",
    "data = np.load(\"invdat7.npy\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 93,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# data = np.load(\"invdat5.npy\")\n",
    "# data = data[:250]\n",
    "n = 10\n",
    "m = 4\n",
    "#data = np.random.normal(0,3,(400,m))\n",
    "data = data_modes(300,m,[10,20,30,40])\n",
    "#restate the ellipsoidal set\n",
    "u = lro.UncertainParameter(m,\n",
    "                                uncertainty_set = lro.Ellipsoidal(p=2, \n",
    "                                                                  rho=1., data =data, loss =loss))\n",
    "# K = 1\n",
    "# u = lro.UncertainParameter(m,\n",
    "#                                 uncertainty_set = lro.MRO(p=2, K = K,\n",
    "#                                                                   rho=1., data =data, loss =loss, uniqueA = True))\n",
    "# Astart = u.uncertainty_set._init_A\n",
    "# formulate cvxpy variable\n",
    "L = cp.Variable()\n",
    "s = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "y = cp.Variable(n)\n",
    "Y = cp.Variable((n,m))\n",
    "\n",
    "# formulate problem constants\n",
    "C = 2000\n",
    "c = np.random.uniform(300,500,n)\n",
    "Q = np.random.uniform(-2,2,(n,m))\n",
    "d = np.random.uniform(100,200,n)\n",
    "t = np.random.uniform(1,3,n)\n",
    "h = np.random.uniform(1,3,n)\n",
    "r = np.random.uniform(20,40,n)\n",
    "# np.save(\"c.npy\", c)\n",
    "# np.save(\"Q.npy\", Q)\n",
    "# np.save(\"d.npy\", d)\n",
    "# np.save(\"t.npy\", t)\n",
    "# np.save(\"h.npy\", h)\n",
    "# np.save(\"r.npy\", r)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# formulate objective\n",
    "objective = cp.Minimize(L)\n",
    "\n",
    "# formulate constraints\n",
    "constraints = [-r@y - r@Y@u + (t+h)@s <= L]\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    constraints += [y[i]+Y[i]@u <= s[i]]\n",
    "    constraints += [y[i]<= d[i]+ (Q[i] - Y[i])@u]\n",
    "constraints += [np.ones(n)@s == C]\n",
    "constraints += [s <=c, s >=0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# formulate Robust Problem\n",
    "prob = lro.RobustProblem(objective, constraints)\n",
    "target = -0.15\n",
    "# solve\n",
    "s = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "init = sc.linalg.sqrtm(sc.linalg.inv(np.cov(data.T)))\n",
    "init_bval = -init@np.mean(data, axis=0)\n",
    "result1 = prob.train(lr = 0.000001, step=500, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = 0.3*init, init_b = 0.3*init_bval, fixb = False, init_lam = 100, target_cvar = target, init_alpha = -0.05, mu_multiplier = 1.01)\n",
    "df1 = result1.df\n",
    "A_fin = result1.A\n",
    "b_fin = result1.b\n",
    "\n",
    "result3 = prob.train(eps = True, lr = 0.00001, step=500, momentum = 0.8, optimizer = \"SGD\", seed = s, init_A = 0.3*init, init_b =0.3*init_bval,  init_lam = 100, target_cvar = target, init_alpha = -0.05, mu_multiplier = 1.01)\n",
    "df_r2 = result3.df\n",
    "\n",
    "# Grid search epsilon\n",
    "result4 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.01, 3, 40), init_A = 0.3*init, init_b = 0.3*init_bval, seed = s, init_alpha = 0.)\n",
    "dfgrid = result4.df\n",
    "\n",
    "result5 = prob.grid(epslst = np.linspace(0.01,3, 40), init_A = A_fin, init_b = b_fin, seed = s, init_alpha = 0.)\n",
    "dfgrid2 = result5.df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 112,
   "metadata": {},
